\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 b. There was the promise of }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 the promised land}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (Canaan) (v. 8). Note that God also established }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 the promised land}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  as an everlasting covenant. Abraham and his descendants are to possess the land forever. But again, the everlasting, eternal reference must apply to the eternal land of Canaan, to heaven itself. Heaven is the only world that is eternal, that will last forever. The promised land is given to all Jews and Gentiles who believe and follow after God just as Abraham did. God is the God of those who believe in Him and follow Him. True, He wants to be the God of unbelievers, but unbelievers do not believe in Him. They will not let Him be their God. Consequently, God is not the God of unbelievers: the promised land is not theirs eternally. Unbelievers may possess it now, during this world, but they will not possess it eternally, in the perfect world that is coming. (See outline and notes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 12:1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super c}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  for more discussion.)\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.6-8&off=2972&ctx=lso%E2%80%9D+(Ro.+4:3%2c+11).%0a~b.+There+was+the+pro"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 83). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 God gave Abraham the sign or ritual of the covenant: circumcision. The outline of the Scripture is self-explanatory:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 1)\tab Circumcision was to include all male children (v. 10).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 2)\tab Circumcision was a sign of the covenant and only a sign (v. 11). It was a sign that a person was dedicating and committing his life to believe the promises (covenant) of God and to follow after God with his whole heart.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 3)\tab Circumcision was to be performed at a set time: when the child was eight days old (v. 12).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 4)\tab Circumcision was to include every household: every male, free or enslaved (vv. 12}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super b}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \endash 13).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 5)\tab Circumcision was to be an everlasting sign (v. 13}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super b}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). What does this mean? How could a physical, earthly, temporal sign be an everlasting sign? It can\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t. Even common sense tells us this. Nothing on this earth lasts forever. God is referring to the meaning lying behind the sign or ritual, referring to the covenant itself. The sign was to remind believers of God\u8217\'92s great covenant established with Abraham \u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1440\li1440\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \bullet \tab that the promised seed was assured; the Savior would come to the earth, and there would always be a nation of believers who followed after God just as Abraham did, a nation of genuine believers who would live forever.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1440\li1440\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \bullet \tab that the promised land was assured; the true children of Abraham would inherit the land, an eternal land forever and ever.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 6)\tab Circumcision was to be strictly observed: refusal to share in the ritual was to be severely punished. A man who refused to be circumcised was to be cut off from the people. This meant that the person was to be removed from those who believed the covenant and followed after God, cut off from those who walked after the faith of Abraham.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . What does the ritual of circumcision say to believers today?}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (1)\tab Jesus Christ has performed a }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 spiritual circumcision}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  upon believers. He has circumcised the believer, cut away the whole sinful nature of the believer. He cuts away more than just a piece of flesh; He performs radical surgery: He cuts away the whole body of sin, all the sin which the believer has committed and for which he stands guilty\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.9-14&off=696&ctx=+that+is+to+come%0ab.+~God+gave+Abraham+the"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 83\endash 84). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Circumcision\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s true circumcision\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 is of the heart, not of the flesh. God never intended circumcision to be only a ritual, a physical sign that one belonged to the people of God. Yes, circumcision was to be a sign, but a sign of spiritual truth: a sign that a person\u8217\'92s heart belonged to God, totally and wholly, a sign that one was following and living for God, fully and completely.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.9-14&off=3106&ctx=(Col.+2:11%E2%80%9312).%0a(2)+~Circumcision%E2%80%94God%E2%80%99s+t"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 84). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
