\par\pard\plain \li1080\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Warren Wiersbe says this about the believer\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s spiritual circumcision:}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i1 What does all of this [circumcision] mean to Christian believers today?\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8230\'85 We have experienced a \u8220\'93spiritual circumcision\u8221\'94 (Col. 2:9\endash 12) that makes us part of the \u8220\'93true circumcision\u8221\'94 (Ph. 3:1\endash 3). When we trusted Christ to save us, the Spirit of God performed \u8220\'93spiritual surgery\u8221\'94 that enables us to have victory over the desires of the old nature and the old life. Circumcision removes only a part of the body, but the true \u8220\'93spiritual circumcision\u8221\'94 puts off \u8220\'93the body of the sins of the flesh\u8221\'94 (Col. 2:11) and deals radically with the sin nature}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i1 This \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93spiritual circumcision\u8221\'94 is accomplished at conversion when the sinner believes in Christ and is baptized by the Spirit into the body of Christ (1 Co. 12:13). This baptism identifies the believer with Christ in His death, burial, resurrection, and ascension, and also in His circumcision (Col. 2:11\endash 12; Luke 2:21). It is not \u8220\'93the circumcision of Moses\u8221\'94 but \u8220\'93the circumcision of Christ\u8221\'94 that is important to the Christian believer}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.9-14&off=4045&ctx=t+live%E2%80%9D+(De.+30:6).%0a~Warren+Wiersbe+says+"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 84). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
