\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Sara\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Family}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 : How can we arouse our faith, have a fresh, stirring experience with God? Step six is to change our relationship to our family.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 a. Note that God honored Sara, greatly honored her. Did Abraham harbor feelings against Sara, secretly blaming her for not being able to bear children? Did he treat her like he should, in love and respect? Was his relationship with her as strong as it should have been? We know that he mistreated her on two occasions, once before this encounter with God and once after (Ge. 12:11\endash 16; 20:2\endash 18). Whatever the case, God honored Sara, and He instructed Abraham to so honor her.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 1)\tab God gave }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Sara}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  a new name, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sarah,\u8221\'94 and He told Abraham to call Sara by that name. \u8220\'93Sarah\u8221\'94 means }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 princess}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Abraham was hereafter to look upon Sarah as a princess, and he was to call and treat her like a princess.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.15-18&off=13&ctx=30:6).%0a6+(17:15%E2%80%9318)+~Sara%E2%80%94Family:+How+can"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 85). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Every husband should treat his wife with respect and love, especially if she is a true believer and follower of God. The Christian wife has the promises of God at her disposal. She can claim God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises and bring great blessing upon the family. Thus, she should be treated as the princess of the family and household.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 2}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . If the Christian husband wants an aroused faith, a fresh, stirring experience with God, he may need to change his relationship with his wife. He may need to change his behavior toward her, begin to treat her with a renewed love and respect, treat her as the princess of the home.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.15-18&off=2138&ctx=kings+of+the+earth.%0a~Thought+1.+Every+hus"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 86). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Note that Abraham worshipped in astonishment and prayer (vv. 17\endash 18). He fell to his face again, utterly astonished, laughing with joy and rejoicing flooding his heart. A believer who has been broken, truly broken, while God is flooding him with assurance knows what Abraham was experiencing. He was astonished, just amazed that such a thing could be. Note that he }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 thought to himself}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , wondered at what he had heard:}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93How can Sarah and I have a child? I am one hundred and Sarah is ninety years old. Such is just too wonderful to be true. But it is true, for God has promised it.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 But then, within just a few moments, Abraham thought of his son Ishmael, the only son he had ever known, the son who was then thirteen years old and whom he had grown to love, the son whom he had thought was to be }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 the promised seed}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . It dawned upon Abraham that his relationship with Ishmael was being changed, that Ishmael was not the promised seed. He had been wrong about Ishmael: all his hopes and dreams had been wrapped up in the boy, misplaced and out of line with God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s will. Immediately, Abraham cried out for God to also bless Ishmael, that God would not forget the son whom he loved so much, that God might let Ishmael live under His very special blessing (v. 18).}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Every father should love his children as Abraham loved Ishmael, and he should cry out for God to bless his children, to bless them in a very special way. In fact, a father must love and pray for his children before God will ever arouse his faith, before God will ever give him a fresh, stirring experience with Himself\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.15-18&off=3643&ctx=to+a+holocaust.5%0ab.+~Note+that+Abraham+wo"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 86). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He drove His will into Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Sarah was to bear a son, the promised seed (v. 19).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab the son was to be named Isaac (note that God Himself named the son, v. 19).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab the covenant established with Isaac was to be an everlasting covenant (v. 19).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Ishmael was to be blessed, especially blessed, in answer to Abraham\u8217\'92s prayer: Ishmael was to become a great nation of twelve rulers (v. 20).}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Note that God reconfirmed His will a third time in verse 21: the covenant of the promised seed and promised land was to be established with Isaac, not with Ishmael nor with anyone else. The promised Savior was to come through Isaac and his descendants, the Jews. As Scripture clearly says, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Salvation is of the Jews\u8221\'94 (Jn. 4:22). Note also that God set the time for Isaac\u8217\'92s birth: he was to be born about one year later (v. 21).}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . We must follow the example of Abraham: accept and surrender to the will and purpose of God. Whatever God calls us to do, we must do it. We must surrender to His will for our lives. This is the only way we can ever have an aroused faith. God cannot give us a fresh, stirring experience with Himself unless we surrender to His will.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.19-21&off=530&ctx=s+will+and+purpose%3b+~He+drove+His+will+in"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 86\endash 87). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Decision\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 Obedience}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 : How can we arouse our faith, have a fresh, stirring experience with God? Step eight is to make a public decision and obey God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s instructions, His Word. Note: as soon as God had finished speaking with Abraham, Abraham got up and acted: he took his whole household and did exactly what God said to do. He obeyed God\u8217\'92s instructions, God\u8217\'92s Word. His decision was made public, for God\u8217\'92s instructions were to involve the whole household.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 a. Abraham led his whole household to obey God, to enter into the covenant relationship: all the men and boys were circumcised (v. 22).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 b. He took the lead, setting the example in the covenant relationship at an old age: he was circumcised at age ninety-nine (v. 23).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 c. He led his own child to obey God, to enter into the covenant relationship\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 at the early age of thirteen (v. 25).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 d. The account is reemphasized: to stress the importance of the covenant relationship (v. 27).}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Every adult should make a public decision and obey God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s instructions, His Word. And every adult should lead his or her household to obey God, to enter into the covenant relationship with God: to accept the promised Savior and the promised land of heaven. If we want God to arouse our faith, to give us a fresh, stirring experience with Himself, we must obey His Word. We must publicly act on His Word, witness and bear testimony to our household.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge17.22-27&off=13&ctx=5:24).%0a8+(17:22%E2%80%9327)+~Decision%E2%80%94Obedience:+"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 87). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
